com.sun.enterprise.dependency
Class DependencyResolver

java.lang.Object
  com.sun.enterprise.dependency.DependencyResolver

public class DependencyResolver
extends java.lang.Object

This class is responsible to resolving the chaining of initialization that need to happen so the dependencies between objects are resolved. Dependencies between objects are expressed with @Requires and @Provides api. It is an abstract class as the mechanism to retrieve resources is not provided. Subclasses could use a jndi style mechanism to store and retrieve such resources.

Author:
Jerome Dochez

resolveAndInstantiate

public <T> java.util.List<? extends T> resolveAndInstantiate(java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Class<? extends T>> _services,
                                                             java.util.logging.Logger logger)
                                                  throws ComponentException
Resolves (reoder the list of services so the dependencies are fully satisfied) and instantiate each component using the resolved order. If the components implement the PostConstruct interface, the PostConstruct.postConstruct() will be called.

Parameters:
_services - the unordered list of services type to re-order and instantiate
logger - used to log
Returns:
list of services fully initialized.
Throws:
ComponentException - if the depenency resolution, instantiation or resources injection/extraction failed.

resolve

public <T> java.util.List<java.lang.Class<? extends T>> resolve(java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Class<? extends T>> _services)
                                                     throws ComponentException
Resolves a list of services implementation by ordering them so the inner dependencies of such services (service A needs the output of service B) are satisfied. Each service uses @Requires to declare its dependency on a external resource while it uses @Provides to declare its output.

Parameters:
_services - list of class objects each defining a Service
Returns:
an ordered list of classes that should be used to successfully initialize the services.
Throws:
ComponentException - when the resultion failed
